* ===========================================================================
* MCC_PROBE_X64_TAGS.DTS
* Report the tag set actually present in the x64 CDX containers.
*
* Status:  READ-ONLY PROBE
* Safety:  REPORT_ONLY
* Purpose: Harvest the real x64 CDX tag inventory so mcc_build_x64_lmdb.dts
*          can declare it, rather than assuming it mirrors x32.
* Inputs:  dottalkpp/data/dbf/x64/*.DBF, dottalkpp/data/indexes/x64/*.cdx
* Outputs: transcript only
* Mutation: NONE. No CREATE, no ADDTAG, no BUILDLMDB, no REINDEX.
* Fixture: none touched
* Gate:    none -- read-only
*
* WHY THIS EXISTS
* ---------------
* On 2026-07-14 the x32 run proved the schema notes under-describe the real
* index state. Every CNX CREATE said "file already exists" and every CNX ADDTAG
* said "tag already exists": the containers held tags the build script had never
* declared (STUDENTS had SID MAJOR LNAME FNAME DOB GPA, not just SID).
*
* The script only appeared to work because it was rebuilding containers it had
* not created. Delete the index directory and it would have silently produced a
* thinner index set.
*
* Rather than assume the x64 lane mirrors x32, harvest it. The containers are
* the authority, not the prose.
*
*   DOTSCRIPT TRACE scripts\mcc\mcc_probe_x64_tags.dts OUT tmp\mcc_x64_tags.log
* ===========================================================================

SET ECHO OFF

ECHO ========================================================
ECHO x64 CDX TAG INVENTORY -- read-only probe
ECHO Source of truth: the containers, not the schema notes.
ECHO ========================================================

WORKSPACE CLOSE
SET PATH DBF DBF/x64
SET PATH INDEXES INDEXES/x64
SET PATH LMDB LMDB/x64
ECHO [SETUP] DBF -> DBF/x64   INDEXES -> INDEXES/x64   LMDB -> LMDB/x64

WORKSPACE OPEN DBF
WORKSPACE

ECHO Areas must be under dbf\x64. If they say og, stop -- the slots
ECHO did not switch and this probe is reporting the wrong tables.

ECHO ========================================================
ECHO CDX INFO + TAGS per table
ECHO ========================================================

ECHO --- BUILDING ---
SELECT BUILDING
CDX INFO
CDX TAGS

ECHO --- STUDENTS ---
SELECT STUDENTS
SHOW TABLE
CDX INFO
CDX TAGS

ECHO --- TEACHERS ---
SELECT TEACHERS
CDX INFO
CDX TAGS

ECHO --- COURSES ---
SELECT COURSES
CDX INFO
CDX TAGS

ECHO --- CLASSES ---
SELECT CLASSES
CDX INFO
CDX TAGS

ECHO --- ENROLL ---
SELECT ENROLL
CDX INFO
CDX TAGS

ECHO --- ROOMS ---
SELECT ROOMS
CDX INFO
CDX TAGS

ECHO --- MAJORS ---
SELECT MAJORS
CDX INFO
CDX TAGS

ECHO --- DEPT ---
SELECT DEPT
CDX INFO
CDX TAGS

ECHO --- TERMS ---
SELECT TERMS
CDX INFO
CDX TAGS

ECHO --- STUD_MAJ ---
SELECT STUD_MAJ
CDX INFO
CDX TAGS

ECHO --- TASSIGN ---
SELECT TASSIGN
CDX INFO
CDX TAGS

ECHO ========================================================
ECHO Probe complete. Nothing was mutated.
ECHO
ECHO Send this transcript back. The tag lists above become the
ECHO CDX ADDTAG declarations in mcc_build_x64_lmdb.dts, so that
ECHO script can rebuild the x64 index set from an EMPTY
ECHO indexes/x64 directory -- which is what makes it a fixture
ECHO rebuild lane rather than a REINDEX in disguise.
ECHO ========================================================
